text.tspan: board is physical pin of the package.
Pin name closer to the board is Pin/Port
I2C number 2 is used for the onboard peripherals.
UART number 4 is connected to the second virtual com port of the BlackMagicProbe-debugger.
LEDs in the 7-segment display can be accessed from C-code by, for example, using HAL_GPIO_TogglePin(SEGA_GPIO_Port, SEGA_Pin);
The LED pins are numbered from "SEGA" to "SEGF" and the decimal point is available as "SEGDP"
The push-button pins next to the 7-segment display are named "BTN1" and "BTN2"
